message.content:
cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with data collection in mobile wireless sensor networks.
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of compressive sensing techniques to aggregate data from sensors.
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible category as the paper deals with signal sparsity and data compression.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses a graphical model to model the spatial prior on biker motion.
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possible category as the paper deals with tracking GPS positions of bikes in a race.
